title: NASA unveils strategies to get humans to Mars - The Daily Breeze
text:
NASA has released an outline for human travel to Mars in the next 20 years, but a lack of details might signify instability when it comes to a budget, according to an advocate with the Planetary Society in Pasadena. NASA's report titled “ Journey to Mars: Pioneering the Next Steps in Space Exploration” , aligns the space agency to the goal of putting humans on Mars by the 2030s without focusing much on the costs or the feasibility.
 The Daily Breeze.
